function clean_column(col::String)
    return replace(lowercase(strip(col)), r"[\s-]" => "_")
end
```

This function uses `lowercase` to convert all characters of the string to lowercase, `strip` to remove leading and trailing whitespaces, and `replace` to replace any spaces or hyphens with underscores. The regular expression `r"[\s-]"` is used to match any whitespace or hyphen character.
